@node modes "JPBoot help-guide v1.0"
@{b}JPBoot help-guide v1.0@{ub}

@{b}Screenmodes@{ub}


Only AGA modes are here, sorry.  If you are using graphics-card, please take
a look at the cards manual for screenmode. You  can also  use  GetModeID  or
similar program to figure out the screenmodeID.

Remember!! The screenmodeID for JPBoot MUST be in hex-format.


VIDEO monitors:

Default monitor.........................00000000
NTSC monitor............................00011000
PAL monitor.............................00021000


The following 6 composite  keys  are  for  modes  on  the  default  monitor.
NTSC & PAL 'flavors' of these particular keys may be made by OR'ing the NTSC
or PAL monitor with the desired mode.

For example, to specifically open a  PAL  high-res  interlaced  screen,  you
would use the 'SCREENMODEID' of 00021000 | 00008004 = 00029004.


VIDEO modes:

Lores...................................00000000
Hires...................................00008000
Superhires..............................00008020
Loreslace...............................00000004
Hireslace...............................00008004
Superhireslace..........................00008024


VGA modes:

VGA monitor.............................00031000

VGAextralores...........................00031004
VGAlores................................00039004
VGAproduct..............................00039024
VGAextraloreslace.......................00031005
VGAloreslace............................00039005
VGAproductlace..........................00039025


A2024 modes:

A2024 monitor...........................00041000

A2024 10Hz..............................00041000
A2024 15Hz..............................00049000


Other modes:

EURO72 monitor..........................00061000

EURO72extralores........................00061004
EURO72lores.............................00069004
EURO72product...........................00069024
EURO72extraloreslace....................00061005
EURO72loreslace.........................00069005
EURO72productlace.......................00069025


EURO36 monitor..........................00071000

EURO36lores.............................00071000
EURO36hires.............................00079000
EURO36superhires........................00079020
EURO36loreslace.........................00071004
EURO36hireslace.........................00079004
EURO36superhireslace....................00079024


SUPER72 monitor.........................00081000


DBLNTSC monitor.........................00091000

DBLNTSClores............................00091000
DBLNTSCloresff..........................00091004
DBLNTSCloreslace........................00091005
DBLNTSChires............................00099000
DBLNTSChiresff..........................00099004
DBLNTSChireslace........................00099005
DBLNTSCextralores.......................00091200
DBLNTSCextraloresff.....................00091204
DBLNTSCextraloreslace...................00091205


DBLPAL monitor..........................000a1000

DBLPALlores.............................000a1000
DBLPALloresff...........................000a1004
DBLPALloreslace.........................000a1005
DBLPALhires.............................000a9000
DBLPALhiresff...........................000a9004
DBLPALhireslace.........................000a9005
DBLPALextralores........................000a1200
DBLPALextraloresff......................000a1204
DBLPALextraloreslace....................000a1205
@endnode


@node prefs "JPBoot help-guide v1.0"
@{b}JPBoot help-guide v1.0@{ub}

@{b}Preferences (S:JPBoot.prefs)@{ub}


FONT=cgtriumvirate.font         ; Font to be used. Must be in FONTS:  drawer
				; or in ROM.
				; Default is topaz.

FONTSIZE=25                     ; Font height.
				; Default is 8.

SCREENMODEID=00029004           ; @{"Screenmode" link modes} to be used.
				; Default is 00029004 (PAL hires-laced).

WIDTH=640                       ; Screen width.
				; Default is 640.

HEIGHT=512                      ; Screen height.
				; Default is 512.

DELAY=30                        ; Waiting  time  in   secs   before   JPBoot
				; automatically selects 'Normal Startup'.
				; Useless if you use ASKUSERNAME option.
				; Default is 30.

ASKUSERNAME=Y or N              ; Ask password at startup?

ALLOWVISITORS=Y or N            ; People without an account can enter?

USESCREEN=Y or N                ; Use screen?

BORDERBLANK=Y or N              ; Blank screen borders?

SAVETIME=Y or N                 ; Save last login time and display it during
				; booting?

INFO=Y or N                     ; Just displays some information.
				; Do not set this to  Y,  try  it  from  the
				; commandline.

AFTERLOCK=Y or N                ; Lock devices AFTER startup? If you want to
				; lock devices which be mounted in  startup-
				; sequence (eg. RAD:,  SD0:  or  VD0:),  you
				; need set this to Y.

VISITORLOCK=HD0:|HD1:|HD2:|SD0: ; If visitor, write-protect these drives.

NORMALLOCK=HD0:                 ; Normal user, write-protect these.
@endnode


@node history "JPBoot help-guide v1.0"
@{b}JPBoot help-guide v1.0@{ub}

@{b}History@{ub}


These first can be forgotten...

- 0.1 - 1.9     No public versions.

- 2.0           First public version.  Buggy,  slow,  poorly  written  shit.
		Do not even try it if you found it somewhere.

- 3.0 - 3.9     3.0 is completely rewritten. No public versions.


...and there actually starts the history.

- 4.0           Completely rewritten.  No  public  version.  Added  Adduser,
		Removeuser and Showusers programs.

- 4.1           Added AFTERBOOT option, some bugfixing. Added WhoAmi, Login,
		and Checkuser programs.
@endnode
